Defendant in custody on another matter.
On count 3, deliver Morphine, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of six (6) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination of both;
2) Maintain absolute sobriety;
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) no contact with any bars or liquor stores;
7) AODA assessment and follow through.
On counts 1 and 4, deliver schedule II non-narcotic and bail jumping, sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served on count 3 of this case, to commence upon defendants discharge date after extended supervision ends.
Conditions of probation:
1) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination of both;
2) Maintain absolute sobriety;
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) no contact with any bars or liquor stores;
7) AODA assessment and follow through;
8) Pay restitution of $827.50 to Shopko at 3415 Calumet Avenue, Manitowoc, WI.  Att: Star Buss.
$50.00 cash bail is ordered applied to restitution.
Minutes.
